#15005

Node curve animation bugfix in cocos 3.10.

There is a bug in the case of nodeCurve animation of Aimate3D.

There is a transform of the node in the c3b. (This name is A)
and transform of animation are there in the c3b. (This name is B)
A and B are the same transform.

The animation data at zero frame contains the transform of the node.
In the original source code , transform of the node will be multiplied twice.
(node transform \* animation transform)

But, Sprite3D root node must do the calculation of the transform.
Reason is that the operation of the transform information in non-animated .
(For example, an application programmer change the position to use the API of Sprite3D :: setPosition.)

In conclusion , it is necessary to change the calculation in Sprite3D root node and Sprite3D children  node.

In the case of Sprite3D root node.

```
void Animate3d::update(float t)
{
    // ...
                for (const auto& it : _nodeCurves)
                {
                    // ...
                    node->setAdditionalTransform(&transform);
                }
}
```

In the case of Sprite3D children node.

```
void Animate3d::update(float t)
{
    // ...
                for (const auto& it : _nodeCurves)
                {
                    // ...
                    node->setNodeToParentTransform(transform);
                }
    // ...
}
```

Was trying to use some binary fonts when, for some reason, the fonts came out with no fontSize.  I noticed in BMFontConfiguration::parseConfigFile that it would read the fontSize from the text version but it would never set it from the binary version.

I just added these lines to BMFontConfiguration::parseBinaryConfigFile.

``` C
uint16_t fontSize = 0; memcpy(&fontSize, pData, 2);  // add
_fontSize = fontSize;  // add
 _padding.top = (unsigned char)pData[7];
_padding.right = (unsigned char)pData[8];
_padding.bottom = (unsigned char)pData[9];
_padding.left = (unsigned char)pData[10];
```

